1. if with_per_connection_event_buffer_size is the default (7), the stalling is severe:
- the swarm halts and does not recover,
2. even if with_per_connection_event_buffer_size is very large (e.g. 7000), the stalling still happens:
- but now it's the other peers that try to connect that cannot connect until the heave connection is dropped
3. stalling does not seem to be dependent on the length of the streams:
- 4 responses per stream stalls the same way as 40 or 400
- even only 1 response per stream stalls the same way
4. TODO: check if the same happens with request-response
